The paper deals with the problem of finding the maximum coverage in a data stream model, which is a classic problem in computer science. The paper uses techniques from data structures, algorithms, and information theory to design algorithms with approximation guarantees. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also uses techniques from machine learning and statistics to analyze the performance of the algorithms, so cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible sub-categories.
